From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <ge-proton@example.com>
Date: Mon, 6 Jul 2026 15:50:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] winepulse: Skip unchanged DualSense mono stream reconnects.

Spider-Man Remastered can crash while opening if the DualSense mono
speaker stream is torn down and recreated as the first non-silent effect
burst starts.  The refresh path is still needed after controller
hotplug, but it should not reconnect a stream that is already ready,
already using the selected Pulse sink, and still on the current hotplug
generation.

Keep forced refreshes for real device changes, but make the unchanged
case a no-op.
---
 dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
index 11111111111..22222222222 100644
--- a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
+++ b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
@@ -3330,7 +3330,7 @@ static HRESULT pulse_dualsense_mono_reconnect_internal(struct pulse_stream *stre
 
     if (pulse_stream_ready(stream))
         current_device = pa_stream_get_device_name(stream->stream);
-    if (!force && current_device && !strcmp(current_device, device) && !strcmp(stream->device, device)
+    if (current_device && !strcmp(current_device, device) && !strcmp(stream->device, device)
             && stream->haptic_hotplug_generation == generation)
     {
         stream->haptic_reconnect_time = 0;
-- 
2.50.0

